  <h2>Understanding the Welsh System</h2>
  <p>The Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016 is the governing legislation for residential tenancies in Wales (effective December 2022). Key features of the Welsh system:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>"Contract-holders"</strong> not "tenants"</li>
    <li><strong>"Occupation contracts"</strong> not "tenancy agreements"</li>
    <li><strong>Rent Smart Wales registration</strong> is mandatory</li>
    <li><strong>Minimum 6 months notice</strong> for no-fault eviction (Section 173)</li>
    <li><strong>Written statement</strong> must be provided within 14 days</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Rent Smart Wales - Critical Requirement</h2>
  <div class="danger">
    <strong>⚠️ You CANNOT serve a valid Section 173 notice unless registered with Rent Smart Wales.</strong>
    <p>If you're not registered:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your notice will be invalid</li>
      <li>Court will dismiss your claim</li>
      <li>You may face prosecution and fines up to £10,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Register at: <strong>rentsmartswales.gov.wales</strong></p>
  </div>

  <h2>Section 173 vs Fault-Based Notices</h2>

  <h3>Section 173 (No-Fault)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Minimum 6 months notice required</li>
    <li>Cannot be served in first 6 months of contract</li>
    <li>No reason required</li>
    <li>Accelerated procedure available (no court hearing)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Fault-Based (Sections 157, 159, 161, 162)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Section 157: Serious rent arrears (2+ months)</li>
    <li>Section 159: Breach of contract</li>
    <li>Section 161: Anti-social behaviour</li>
    <li>Section 162: Contract-holder's notice to leave</li>
    <li>Shorter notice periods possible</li>
    <li>Must prove the ground at court</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
  <div class="highlight">
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Not being registered with Rent Smart Wales</strong> - Fatal to any claim</li>
      <li><strong>Wrong notice form</strong> - Use prescribed Welsh forms (RHW series)</li>
      <li><strong>Serving too early</strong> - Cannot serve Section 173 in first 6 months</li>
      <li><strong>Wrong notice period</strong> - Must be at least 6 months for Section 173</li>
      <li><strong>Poor service records</strong> - Keep detailed evidence of how and when notice was served</li>
      <li><strong>Missing written statement</strong> - Must have been provided within 14 days of occupation</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <h2>Strengthening Your Case</h2>
